---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 6
  Paragraph: 26
Title: The Great And Venerable Teacher
---
All at once Master Yu fell ill. Master Ssu went to ask how he was.
"Amazing" said Master Yu. "The Creator is making me all crookedy like
this! My back sticks up like a hunchback and my vital organs are on top
of me. My chin is hidden in my navel, my shoulders are up above my
head, and my pigtail points at the sky. It must be some dislocation of
the yin and yang!"
